.TH RIND-RUN0 1 "2026-06-07" "rind" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rind-run0 \- escalate to root privileges
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rind run0
.RI [ command " " [ args... ]]
.br
.B run0
.RI [ command " " [ args... ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rind run0
 authenticates the current user and, upon success, executes the given
.I command
as root (uid 0, gid 0).
.PP
When invoked directly as
.B run0
(e.g., via a symlink), the command arguments are taken from the command line directly.
.PP
Authentication is performed by prompting for the root password over the terminal. The password is sent to the daemon's
.B run0
IPC endpoint, which validates credentials through the privilege runtime.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I command
The program to execute as root.
.TP
.I args
Arguments passed to
.IR command .
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
rind run0 /bin/bash
rind run0 dmesg \-w
run0 ls /root
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The executed command inherits the current working directory, environment variables, and standard I/O from the calling process.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rind (1),
.BR rind-syssess (1)
